China Mobile, Esprit, Sun Hung Kai: Hong Kong Equities Preview

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-09-16T00:51:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/china-mobile-esprit-sun-hung-kai-hong-kong-equities-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in Hong Kong trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  rose 0.7 percent to 19,181.50. The Hang
Seng China Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, increased 0.8 percent to 10,051.67.  China Mobile Ltd. (941)  (941 HK): The mobile-phone company aims
to work with Apple Inc. (APPL US) on an alliance that may lead
to an iPhone for the company’s fourth-generation TD-LTE network,
Chairman  Wang Jianzhou  said. The stock gained 0.1 percent to
HK$79.95.  Esprit Holdings Ltd. (330)  (330 HK): The clothing retailer that
reported a 98 percent plunge in its full-year profit yesterday
is hiring a new manager for China as it plans to more than
double sales there in four years, according to Chief Executive
Officer Ronald Van der Vis. The stock tumbled 18 percent to
HK$15.08.  Great Wall Motor Co. (2333 HK): The Chinese maker of  pickup
trucks  said it will sell as many as 304.2 million shares for
between 13 yuan and 14 yuan apiece. The stock advanced 2.3
percent to HK$10.54.  Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd. (16)  (16 HK): The world’s biggest
developer by market value said its full-year underlying profit
rose 55 percent HK$21.5 billion ($2.76 billion) after home sales
and rental income increased. The stock gained 1.5 percent to
HK$102.40.  United Co. Rusal (486 HK): The Russia-based producer of the
metal is in talks with the Italian government to restart the
EurAllumina refinery in Sardinia. Rusal is “exploring various
opportunities” to resume operations, the company said in an e-
mailed response to queries from Bloomberg. The stock was
unchanged at HK$8.06.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in  Hong Kong  at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 